The position of the ode in the book is thought by many to be due to the same cause3 but it is more probable that Horace placed it and its companion ode, the fifteenth, at the end, that he might close the book with the Emperor's praise. The date of composition must be about the same as that of the fourth ode, ie. 14 nc. Metre, 68.
